So here are few points:  1-The name of days are appearing in each box, this seems ridiculous. It makes its appearance very clumsy and over populated. It should be at top because there is no way that different days will appear in one column. It should be as it appears in the widget type ‚ÄúMonth‚Äù. When it can be there why it cannot be here also.  2-Another strange thing I noticed that the date appears in the right bottom corner. I am in doctor‚Äôs office and the next appointment she is booking is in July next year. Now to choose a date I need to jump in July next year to see which day/date suits both of us. Intuitive for a click and hold on the event to drag between daily/weekly views. As this command is currently how we access the new event /paste option. I suggest a single tap of the event or time block to continue doing what it does now except add the new event/paste buttons where the cut, copy functions are. I believe this would be more intuitive. Alternatively, the new event/paste options can appear near the pop-up bubble with event details. I am hopeful of changes to allow more intuitive use for those seeking an all inclusive replacement for Google calendar and other popular alternatives. I see digical having the most potential.

Great app.  (See my review for the base app in addition to this review for the + Key.)   NOTE: If you ever have to change your Google email address, as I did, you will need to uninstall the DigiCal+ Key "app" and re-install it.  The Key contains the email address you used when you purchased it, and the goofy DigiCal app uses that to validate your + Key with Google Play -- the only app that I've bought that does that.  All the other paid apps are actually separate apps, rather than a base app and a premium key.  I don't like to keep my calendars on servers, I keep them on my phone and back things up to a shared drive (like a Briefcase concept). Great app...!!
Great app but can you add option to pick the today text colour in the grid view too? Thanks!

Its a very nice looking app and it works well on my Note 3.  I only have 1 wish to make it 5 stars: Choose which calendar to appear in the widget.  I have 3 calendars I like to see in Calendar view but not in the widget and there's no way to hide the calendars you don't want to see.  Otherwise, solid app!
Didn't need the pro features, just loved the app.
This app has great features and a nice user interface.  Highly recommended
I love this app but would love to see this integrate with Google Tasks so i can see them right along side of my calendar.  PLEASE add this to the app!!!
Worth the money for me. Feature rich & good looking. Use daily to stay on top of it all.  Note 2
Worth every penny. Nice, clean looking widgets.
The only thing that I would love to see is the ability to add attachments to an appointment... Maybe I missed it.  But if that happens, this already awesome app would be that much more perfect.
Can you make it so once an event has passed it can become dark or something showing it past. This is available in the calendar but not the widget.
Amazing app. Had a little bug and the support team helped right away. Thanks Albert!
The best calendar that I have tried so far.
Love this

This is a great app. Easy to use and easy on the eyes. I like the customization. Only reason I do not give it a 5 star rating, on my Droid Bionic, I have to go in manually and select my work calender. It does not sync on its own. Maybe its my  phone been old but it is running the latest upgrade.
Syncs directly and fast with Google calendar with a stunning visual interface.  Very clear read on both phone and tablets.  Well thought out widgets make this an app I recommend.  Thank you.

Pretty looking, but the "unlocked" app was Not worth it. Actually very limited functions. No repeated events when adding new events, this is a Basic function, without it it's broken. Month view does not scroll. Can't set which days are weekend, when weekend starts. I could go on... Apparently their "todo list" is not a priority either. No action on updates or new features.
replyContent: I am sorry to hear that you're disappointed. It's already possible to add repeated events and the month widget will become scrollable in the next update.

content: Easy to use

I'm so thankful to have found a calendar that actually works for me. Most of the other available agenda/calendar apps I've tried either don't have some of the functionality I need or are so cumbersome they're too much of a hassle to use. DigiCal is the perfect balance of functionality and style. It's definitely worth the money and you'll be supporting an active and responsive developer.

Got Digical to replace old calendar app that was getting buggy.  Have Digical on both tablet and phone but they rarely are in sync.  I have to manually refresh the app to get them lined up.  Changes I made yesterday on the tablet or Google calendar on the PC are not showing up on the phone.  Also needs better snooze options, 10 minutes is not enough most of the time.  Multiple options are needed.  Otherwise, I like the widgets a lot and the overall ease of use is good but with syncing issues it makes it hard to rely on.  Here's hoping for some improvements.
Love everything about the app & widget just wish we could scroll through the months on the widget please allow this feature then will give 5 stars
I would give 5 stars if I could sync instead of entering events 2 times. I am awaiting response from developer...
replyContent: Hi Linda, here's a help page explaining how to sync on multiple devices. https://digibites.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/articles/200347163-How-do-I-sync-DigiCal-with-multiple-Android-devices-

content: I am replacing Business Calendar with Digical. The only thing it's missing seems to be scrolling in widgets.

This is the best looking and well thought out calendar I have used on a smartphone. The only issue I have with it is the repeated events are limited to a small number of choices and the latest Google Calendar allows you to set the days, number of weeks, number of months...
I love this app paid for the upgrade a long time ago, had no issues ever until the latest version. Now my edit time isn't working... Pls fix!
Badly needs month view widget in the same format as in the app.
So far it has been a NIGHTMARE it has hid itself so I can not see it or use it, what a rip OFF
replyContent: Hi Ralph, we can help you if you send us an email to digical@digibites.nl

content: Can you please add an option to snooze events for an hour or at least add a shortcut to edit the events from the reminder popup?!? 10 minutes doesn't always cut it. Other than that it's the perfect calendar app. I love the widgets. Just needs more options once the reminder alarms pop up. A dismiss button for individual snoozed alarms would be nice also.
A calendar app as good as iOS.

I have tried Samsung S planner, aCalendar, and others and Digical wins hands down. I bought the paid version. Great flexibility in repeating events, superb weekly agenda view, very useful widgets (I have a 6 and a 15 day widgets) that start Today, and they are very responsive: I had a.problem.with Exchange view of Digical events, and they fixed it in 2 days.

But it's a BIG shame that you can't COLOR your events = the text, either by highlight it or just the text itself, unlike most other calendars, I've tried, for example Google calendar: but not transparent. I choosed this calendar due to the BEAUTIFUL, AND the transparent look. I'm currently looking for another calendar however. Everything has the same color. This makes the overview for example in month wiev from home screen, very difficult.  Uninstalling.
replyContent: I am sorry to hear that you are disappointed by our calendar. It's on our todo list to have custom text color ability in the calendar views.

content: Great app... Beautiful and professional looking... worth every penny.  Just wish the month widget allowed users to scroll between months...I'm only able to see the current month. It's there a way to do this that I'm missing?
Very impressed, honestly couldn't ask for more.
Great calendar
Awesome app keeps my life organized best for busy ppl.
i love this calendar it is the best one I have been using since my first Android now works great on my s4
You'll love it

Best calender app on the marke. I'll use it forever, I love the colour collaboration and the widgets. One thing, I wish i could make events reoccur forthnightly. Unless I've missed it,  Can you guys please add this down the track?
Great calendar. Better than stock

I have used a lot of the currently available calendar programs I have just switched over from ACalendar to Digical. What a great program I used it for about an hour and paid for the pro version. the look and feel is second nature to use and the included Widget works flawless Great job
Great app but I would love to see auto refresh

To be frank - after playing with this app for a couple of hours, I have decided to make it my default calendar. Essentially dropping Pocket Informant (incidentally did a bungled up job of getting out a good application and maintaining user loyalty) in its favor...  In my support of the developer, I've even purchased the unlock key.
I've tried lots of different calendars over the years.  No more! Syncs with all my devices and so easy to set up. And updates just keep making it better.  A+
Dev very helpful
replyContent: I am sorry to hear that, can you please contact our support desk by sending us an email to digical@digibites.nl?

content: Presents a large amount of information in numerous clear and concise views.  Options are plentiful to satisfy personal preferences.   Easy integration with Exchange and multiple other calendar sources.    Responsive support.    It is the foundation for wirelessly managing my virtual consulting practice.
DigiCal is one of a dozen apps that I use every day. I didn't need widgets but I bought a license to support development. Keep up the great work!

I bought this because the free app deserved supporting.  Good developer response when I emailed them with a feature that was broken - they pushed out a release fixing it, and numerous other things, within a few days.

Overall is great. Beautiful interface, and good integration with system. Still needs a "share" button for easy sharing of any event (in any view), and an option to select font sizes in Agenda view (stock font is too big), cuz doesn't let you see a considerable amount of events. I'm running Pro version, and there are other free and less-quality apps have this options. Add this and is a 5+ stars.

Hei.  I absolutely LOVE this calendar,  and it is by far the best one I have tried yet (I've been through my share of calendars)  However,  although I love the colour function,  and the fact that there are a great variety of colours to change from.  I would love for a possible customisation in the name of the colours?  So that I know which colours ive used before and for what.  This would make it easier to make new events of the same 'colour'.   Thank you so much for the app. It is great.  =)
One of the best calendar apps out there.   Would like to be able to have the option to show both start and end times in the widget though.
Main app works Ok... But the widget does not show up on screen... I've tried all different sizes.. I can press and hold and remove... But don't see anything there.. Hope this gets fixed soon
replyContent: Could you please contact our support desk: digical@digibites.nl. We can help you fix the problem.

content: Love this app and I have bought a few calendar apps but will be sticking with this one. Five stars if they add a Day picker to reoccurring events menu.

Paid for app and digi+cal won't launch widget won't work at all what does I don't... If someone can tell me what I'm doing wrong I may give app 4-5 stars but if this is a glitch it's not worth the paid download error the application to launcher has stopped unexpectedly. It has never worked and it's been a week now since download
replyContent: Can you please send us an email to digical@digibites.nl? Our support desk will help you solve the problem.

content: This is one of the best business apps on the market. I used the free version for a few weeks. Then decided to purchase it. Money well spent.
Best calendar out there

Utter garbage!  Can't even get the Widget to appear, no matter what I do with the size / settings etc.!  Such a shame as I quite liked the free version!  Avoid like the plague!  One star...as you can't rate it at zero!
replyContent: Could you please send an email to digibites@digical.nl? Our support desk can help you solve the problem.

content: I really like the simplicity of this widget.  I really wish that I could scroll through different months on the widget rather than opening the app every time I need to look ahead to the next month. I'm hoping that the developers have plans to improve this app and add more features.  Otherwise, I may have just wasted 5 bucks.....
Beautiful interface, very nice week view, simple and powerful use. When you add the snooze function for the reminder I will give you five stars
Great calendar app. Widgets are great. Developer is responsive.
This add-on does not work. Tried to add month widget and still states only with digical+. Useless and a waste of hard earned money.
replyContent: Could you please send us an email to digical@digibites.nl? Our support desk can help you.

content: Without a doubt, the best calendar app out there. Love that I have the month view with the days agenda on one screen and the dark theme is easy on the eyes. You've got to give this one a try.

Very good calendar app, simple and clearly organized however I am missing the posibility to set the colors for a special event (e.g. cyan for working hours) and the reminder could offer setting the alarm for some days(to alert only mondays and tuesdays within creating one event)
So far so good.  Love the dark theme,  it also works with my other calender Samsung  Thanks!                                                               CCP
Sweet UI, one of my favorites!! My only issue is that anytime you adjust the look of the widgets, you have to reset all of the settings you had previously set or they will be wiped out.

In my opinion, it's the best calendar app available. Sure it has problems, but for an app still in beta (pre 1.0 anyway) it works really well and has great features. Overall I would highly recommend this app to anyone wanting something other than the official Google app. ***Edit: The most recent update made location search way worse. I used to be able to throw business name and city name in all together and it would find it no problem. Now it's returning results that don't have anything to do with what I am searching for, or it will find the business but in a completely different state. The app is still great, but this definitely kicks it down a notch.
It's almost perfect. I don't like how the widget has transparent lines between days in the Agenda view. Still the best calendar app out there!
Excellent
I already left a review when I first purchased this app. The more I use it the more I love it! I am so glad I took the advice of another user!
This is this the best calendar. It has beautiful widgits. The location info is amazing for making Google now better
Except the price...  Are you serious?!! . Still some bugs in widget customisation. Some colours get reset to default when others get changed.

Very nice calendar,  easy 5*'s. However, I would like see in feature updates the ability to sync my tasks and calendar items from my work email (Exchange account).  Other than, everything else is great. Thanks, keep up the good work.
Excellent
Best calendar I've tried, and I've tried many. It's great. I love the month view with summary at the bottom and the new widgets are beautiful!
Good start but needs some refining
Won't sync if remove the Google official calendar app?
replyContent: Could you please send us an email at digical@digibites.nl and explain your problem? Our support team is glad to help you!

content: This is a very nice application it also works on note2 and it never crashes. People who are using Google calendars to view agendas Tudor Google email I would definitely recommend this out what is more better than any other out there
Awesome
Better than stock calendar. Looks great & easier to use
One of my must have apps.Love the widgets, great customization options concerning both looks and information displayed.
Works well. Nice and configurable. Get rid of the spinning wheels for time setting though - it's annoying.

Very well designed calendar app. Wish I could change text color in the widget. I want the widget to be white (to match the Google Now widget), but the text is white, so I have to use a translucent white Edit: text color selection now available. Great app.
Superb app, one of the best in its class
Very solid app with tons of customizability. The devs are very responsive and are constantly improving the product. What else do you need to say - this app does exactly what you want it to very well.
Use it every day.
Simple and gets the job done.

Great use of locations, nice look and easy to use. Widgets are great also. It is just easy to use. I was using Pocket Informant, but the new version is not as good as the old version and this program is better.

after i created an event on my phone, it's synchronized to my tablet. however the color of the  event just stayed all the same on the tablet calendar even tho i.have used different colors when i created the events initially. otherwise it's a brilliant app
This is all I have been looking for to keep all I have to do together. No other comes close
The best calendar on the play store.

Need to be able to change the calendar for an existing event. Also, I have an HTC One and I have a calendar with all my Facebook friends' birthdays. Would be great to be able to post to their walls directly from the event (the stock HTC One calendar can do this and it's pretty useful). Other than that I love the app.
This is by far the most beautiful and most functional calendar app. I highly recommend it.
Love the colour coding.

This calendar looks great and is easy to use. Its probably the closest calendar to Apples iCal (if your new to Android) and the month widget is beautiful. If they added birthday events then personally this would be the perfect calendar app.

Really like this app. The only thing stopping me from giving it five stars is that appointment notifications don't appear in the lock screen ( I use LockerPro to give iOS style lockscreen notifications ). Every other app seems to work with this, but not Digical.  Apart from that, I really love it!

The Calendar app for me is the most important app on my phone. Digical  for me is the best one so far. The clean interface and the many customizations.Please keep the app updated. One thing I would like to see on the widget is a refresh icon.  Rev:Doesn't need a Refresh icon,the calender updates itself when you enter new data.  5-Stars!!!!!!!!!!
Tried many and thought I had a great one before.  Great layout and widgets. Keep up turgid work!

I too have tried 20 or more calendar apps and I have to say some are old and dated. This app is crisp and fresh. Widget is what I want for my newer phone. The calendars are clear to read. This is the calendar app to get!
The only thing is.. the icon is ugly as sin. Would five star for a better icon.
Why is this not available?!
replyContent: It's now available in the latest version! :)

content: I'm really not a fan of the default calendar apps on Android (both vanilla and Samsung). This takes the best elements of both and offers great customisation and widgets, and guarantees a great calendar no matter what firmware you're running. Excellent value at 99c.
main app looks better than Google's but the agenda widget also need a dark theme
replyContent: You can now customize the list style widget with our color picker!

content: Gladly bought this just for the nice looking full month view calendar widget.

There is nothing much to say other than the widget is superb. I have it on my home screen and it blends very nicely with the desktop.  My favorite features are the UI and map pin next to calendar item.

I previously used Touch Calendar which is great but has limited widget customisation, so didn't quite achieve what I wanted. After trying many apps discovered DigiCal is exactly what I wanted.  Beautiful, customisable (even in its free form) and highly recommend it.
Great app....nitpicking here but I wish the icon was nicer and clearer....looks a little blurry on my HTC One.   Other than that...fantastic app.
Wish you could vertical swipe on the month grid widget to change month... Aside from that no complaints

Best calendar app so far, but i would still like to see a a few changes. 1st, on the day view, get rid of the month calendar at the top as it takes up to much room, if i wanted to see the full month i would go to the month view, 2nd, i would like to be able to set event repeats to bi weekly, 3rd at the most I'm only getting about 7 events on screen in agenda view so i would like to see an option to reduce text size in agenda view. But even as the app stands i still think it's the best calendar app.
Haopy I bought it. Would like the function to display public holidays in your region and have scrollable widgets for paid users

I really love it, minus a few minor things that would give it a 5-star rating:  - Custom color picker for calendars - Tasks integration - Faster response time when swiping from day to day, or month to month, etc... It feels too laggy when I want to swipe between days.  Other than that, it's quite awesome. I love the visual design and the fact that it has a built in notification popup.

.. but is the best Calendar app I've found on Android in 3 years of use. Addition of the month grid in 0.8 is fantastic. One request would be to keep it free of bloat unlike some other cal apps. Cheers.

Hands down the best calendar app for android, it has the best UI, a ton of useful features (not gimmicks), great looking and customizable widgets, and very simple to use. I'm very happy with my purchase.

Had to change from poor to average. Thought it was draining battery, but phone was dying. Ok app. Would be better if resonse time to see widgets was faster and it didnt keep flashing in and out when I first woke the phone.	Samsung Nexus

Excellent app! Bought it. The only missed feature is possibility to customise font size in Text Month and Agenda views. I would expect to see this at least in paid version. Please implement such possibility, as for full HD devices it's extremely important. Otherwise you don't get any benefit from big resolution.

After trying what seems like every calendar app out there, I finally found the best by far. Great UI, options, appearance. Your search is over!!  If I would like to see any changes, it would be the addition of a keypad input for the time entry. Otherwise, perfect.
There are many calendar apps to install and test...some too thin, and most are overkill. This one is the 'just right' of them all.

Beautiful UI and huge list of features and options is what makes this calendar app a must have. I've tried other similar apps in the market but nothing else comes even close. Can't wait to see where this excellent dev takes this in the future.
Works smoothly. Like all the customization.    Would like other colours than the blue  square on today on month view.
I've used it for months. The devs have been great about adding functionality and options. I'm happy to support great work like this. Cheers mates!

Finally an Android calendar that can rival the iOS ones! Very pleased with the intuitive n pleasing layouts. One suggestion is to add options for categories/local calendars so that events can be grouped by colours etc

Really good functionality and works very smooth.  Best is that the developers listen to your feedback if you contact them and add features you miss on any other date-application like the "go-to-date" option.  Awesome!!!
This app is one of the best calendar apps I've used. Great widgets, highly customizable, Google Now integration, and Dev support! Paid version is worth it.
Perfect design and functionality.  And smooth like a ios app.  Did had the choice between a cracked version and the official.  Did decide for the official cuz it's really good!
I emailed dev in regards to black themed widget and received email reply within 20 minutes or so. Attractive app with functionality. Worth the money. Thank you.

I've tried them all over the years. Now I just use digical+. I it's elegant, straightforward and works like a dream. Syncs seamlessly. And while I would someday like to see Google tasks integrated, I love it just way it is right now.  After using it daily for a month, it's just beautiful. It works and is a pleasure to interact with.
It wasn't working for me before but this latest update foxed whatever was wrong with it. Awesome.
Great app. Still needs some improvements here and there, but overall I like it very much. I've sent suggestions to the dev.
Strange bug prevents from displaying (day view) of week 1 of 2013. More detailed month view & browseable + selectable mini calendar in day view would be great!
replyContent: Could you please contact support desk: digical@digibites.nl with your question?

content: Google Tasks integration would be great though.
Makes my life easier!!
Good app.easy to use, that's what I want.
Thanks...etc....

Love this calendar, bought the full version within a day.  Devs are listening and want to keep us happy :-)  Would love having my Google tasks showing on the calendar so I could drop another app all together.  Thanks for thinking of it!
The main icon with the "paid for" icons. There is no reason to have 2 icons for the same app. Uninstalled until that is modified.

More transparency options for widgets, add event directly from widget (goes to widget settings right now instead when tapping pencil sign), option to make Sunday the first day of the week, and dark theme option. Almost there!
PS- Can we get Google Tasks integration?
Only thing on my wish list Is a dark or more transparent widget option.  Near perfect.
This calendar app has a great user interface. It's seems to have regular updates and in my opinion, with some small tweaks, should be the best calendar in the Play store.
